arch:property.oc:show_val: Flot sample 2, (4418), >4mm, 100% diagnostics only A medium size unit of light to medium brown bones. Most of the unit is sheep/goat skull and foot bones with some axial skeleton and some long bone fragments. There are only a few small pieces of identifiable limb bones. There are several worked pieces, including a bit of worked antler. About 10% of the long bone fragments are burnt, and there is a small amount of gnawing and digestion. Trampling and abrasion is also quite low, perhaps a bit more than in some of the other very undisturbed looking deposits. The flotation sample is similar, generally light brown with about 10% burnt. The surface condition of the bones is good, although the pieces are small - many are less than .5 cm. Diagnostics are all sheep/goat. Amphibian and microfauna bones were pulled from both the dry sieve and the flot sample. There was also one human metacarpal in the dry sieve. Last Number = 118

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
